title: D-Day the Sixth of June [1956 - USA] (Robert Taylor) drama
description:
D-Day the Sixth of June (1956 - USA)

Drama / Romance / War

starring . . . . Robert Taylor, Richard Todd, Dana Wynter, Edmond O'Brien
 
http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0049117/


A few hours before D-Day, Special Force Six embarks to destroy an especially well-defended German gun emplacement on the Normandy coast. As the ship steams towards it, the officers and men recall what circumstances brought them there. This is one of few American movies that present a specifically British viewpoint. Major characters are British whilst military forces shown in action are Canadian.
